                "invention-title": [
                    "Melamine-modified carbon dots and application of melamine-modified carbon dots as double-signal fluorescence sensor in salbutamol detection",
                    "三聚氰胺修饰的碳点及其作为双信号荧光传感器在沙丁胺醇检测中的应用"
                ]
            },
            "abstract": [
                {
                    "p": "The invention discloses construction of a dual-signal fluorescence sensor based on melamine modified carbon dots and application of the dual-signal fluorescence sensor in salbutamol detection. Salbutamol molecules can cause aggregation of originally dispersed melamine-modified carbon dots through hydrogen-bond interaction and cause resonance transfer of energy, so that blue fluorescence of the melamine-modified carbon dots is quenched under the irradiation of 365-nanometer exciting light, and yellow fluorescence of the melamine-modified carbon dots is enhanced under the irradiation of 460-nanometer exciting light. The intensity change of the fluorescence of the two colors and the concentration of the salbutamol are in a linear relationship, so that the change of the fluorescence of the different colors under the two exciting lights realizes low-cost and visual quantitative analysis on the salbutamol residue. The double-signal fluorescence sensor has a self-correction function, and the accuracy of a detection result is improved."
                },
                {
                    "p": "本发明公开了一种基于三聚氰胺修饰的碳点的双信号荧光传感器的构建及其在沙丁胺醇检测中的应用。沙丁胺醇分子可通过氢键作用导致原本分散的三聚氰胺修饰的碳点聚集，并引起能量共振转移导致三聚氰胺修饰的碳点在365纳米激发光照射下的蓝色荧光猝灭，在460纳米激发光照射下的黄色荧光增强。两种颜色荧光的强度变化与沙丁胺醇的浓度呈线性关系，由此两种激发光下的不同颜色荧光的变化实现了对沙丁胺醇残留的低成本、可视化定量分析。这种双信号荧光传感器具有自我矫正功能，提高了检测结果精确度。"
                }
            ]
        }
